## Description
Adds fallback spacing for browsers that don't support CSS Grid/Flexbox gap property.

## Problem
- Older mobile browsers don't support gap property
- Layout breaks on older Android devices
- No spacing between grid/flex items
- Poor backwards compatibility

## Solution
- Use @supports to detect gap support
- Add margin-top fallback for older browsers
- Applies to grid and flex containers
- Maintains consistent spacing

## Impact
- Works on older Android devices (< Chrome 84)
- Better backwards compatibility
- Consistent spacing across all devices
- No layout breaks

## Browser Support
- Fallback for Android < 5.0 (Chrome < 84)
- iOS Safari < 14.5
- Older Samsung Internet browsers

